('278', 'Pointe Coupee Electric', 'pcemc', '2506 False River Drive New Roads LA 70760', 'http://www.pcemc.org/', 'P.0 Box 160  New Roads LA 70760', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Nominating Committees made up of Pointe Coupee Electric Members from Districts 3 and 5 met Tuesday Nov. 5 2013 at Pointe Coupee Electric Head-quarters at 2506 False River Drive in New Roads. The purpose of the meeting was to nominate candi-dates for the Board of Directors for terms of three years beginning January 29 2014. The candidates nominated are incumbents George G. LaCour Jr. District 3 and Peter Rumfola Jr. District 5. Pointe Coupee Electric members serving on the nominating committee from Districts 3 and 5 were listed in the October issue of 22 Country. DEADLINE FOR NOMINATING CANDIDATES BY PETITION is Wednesday November 27 2013 at 4:30 P.M. According to the by-laws of Pointe Coupee Elec-tric Membership Corporation candidates to run for the Board can be nominated in two ways: • (1) NOMINATING COMMITTEE of Pointe Coupee Electric Members make recommendations from their district; and • (2) PETITION - Any fifteen (15) members acting together in a district may nominate another candidate by petition not less than fifteen (15) days prior to the elec-tion. NOMINATIONS BY PETITION for candidates in District 3 and 5 are due in the office of Pointe Coupee Electric at 2506 False River Drive New Roads Loui-siana before or by the close of business at 4:30 P.M. Wednesday November 27 2013. Candidates for the Board must be active members of Pointe Coupee Electric and their main residence must be in the district for which they are nominated. Only active members within the same district as the candidate may make nominations. The district number is listed on the far right side of the PCEMC bill in the green shaded area. The list of nominations will be posted in the lobby of the Pointe Coupee Electric office. If there are no nominations by petition the candi-dates placed in nomination by the Nominating Commit-tees will assume their seats on the Board of Directors on January 29 2014. (Acct. No. 2325600) The by-laws regarding elections of Directors of the Pointe Coupee Electric board and the election schedule were published in the October 2013 issue of 22 Country', '', 'http://www.pcemc.org/content/laws', '22'),
